    "This makes pre-RS traceability a more dynamic procedure than post-RS traceability because it has to handle initially unstructured qualitative and varying data of different types and formats [98].",
    "The management and maintenance of trace links face similar challenges to post-RS traceability, such as the detection of obsolete links.The diverse needs of practitioners and their various roles within a project are often considered crucial for determining an appropriate traceability strategy [34,60,75,89].",
